Requirements:
---------------------------------------------------------

-Repertoire AJAX toolkit widgets: all that is needed is the directory /public/javascripts/rep.widgets --copy this to your javascripts directory and you should be all set.
-jQuery >= 1.4.x  (http://jquery.com/)
-jQuery UI >= 1.8.x  (http://jqueryui.com/)
-jQuery 'UI lightness' (http://jqueryui.com/themeroller/ --click on "Gallery" on the left and select UI Lightness)
-Datejs ( http://code.google.com/p/datejs/source/checkout : using Revision #191, 2008-05-12  --MUST REVIEW THIS SO WE CAN DECIDE HOW TO DEAL WITH IT...looks like the last substantial update was 1998...eek.)


Using Repertoire Chronos:
---------------------------------------------------------

Include these two files:
 -javascripts/chronos/jquery.chronos.js
 -javascripts/chronos/timeline.css


You will also need to have included the necessary jQuery and datejs files:

-jquery.js
-jquery-ui.js
-datejs/build/date.js
-datejs/build/time.js
-ui-lightness/jquery-ui.css


So, for example, your html header may include the following lines:

<script src="javascripts/jquery-1.4.2.js"></script>
<script src="javascripts/jquery-ui-1.8.custom.min.js"></script>
<script src="javascripts/datejs/build/date.js"></script>
<script src="javascripts/datejs/build/time.js"></script>
<script src="javascripts/chronos/jquery.chronos.js"></script>
<link media="all" type="text/css" href="javascripts/chronos/timeline.css" rel="Stylesheet" charset="utf-8" />
<link media="all" type="text/css" href="javascripts/ui-lightness/jquery-ui-1.7.2.custom.css" rel="Stylesheet" charset="utf-8" />
